section: compiler
synopsis: Fix a Simplifier panic on open expressions (e.g. in the GHCi debugger)
issues: #17833 #21118
mrs: !16187
description: {
  ``simplifyExpr`` now seeds the Simplifier's in-scope set with the free
  variables of the expression being simplified, restoring the invariant that the
  in-scope set contains all of an expression's free variables. This fixes a panic
  (a failed ``substTy`` assertion) when an open expression reaches the Simplifier,
  as can happen for expressions entered in the GHCi debugger.
}
